                                                                                                                                 2                                                                                        NATION BRIEFS
                              
	 Srinagar, Nov. 7: Hurriyat hawk Syed Ali Shah Geelani today relaxed his Kashmir protest schedule for the first time in the past five turbulent months following demands from the business community, reports our special correspondent.          
	But the announcement of a let-up in the protest calendar  a schedule of demonstrations and marches he draws up and issues every 10 days  came as clashes erupted between mobs and the activists of a pro-Delhi NGO, Forum, that denounced shutdowns.                  
	 Dubai (PTI): India has introduced a 24-hour helpline in Mecca to help Haj pilgrims.The Indian consulate has started helpline service on the numbers 02-5496000 and 02-5458000 at the Indian Haj Mission in Mecca, Indian Haj consul B. S. Mubarak said.                   
	 London (PTI): Britains High Court has upheld home secretary Theresa Mays decision to bar Indian preacher Zakir Naik from entering the UK for lectures. The action against Naik, who was scheduled to arrive in the UK on June 16, has been taken because of his alleged support to Islamic extremism. Naik has denied the allegation.                                                                                                                                              
